                    desired huge pages for each NUMA node.                </p>                                    <p >For each available NUMA node, two fields are supplied, as                        illustrated in the following example screen for two NUMA nodes.</p>                    <fig id="fig_u13_tdf_2r" >                        <image href="jow1424729464258.image" id="image_tcp_tdf_2r"  width="5in">                            <alt >tis-hugepage-memory-dialog</alt>                        </image>                    </fig>                    <dl>                        <dlentry >                            <dt ># of VM 2M Hugepages Node <i >n</i></dt>                            <dd >                                <p >The number of 2MiB pages to reserve for VM use on                                    the NUMA Node. If no 2MiB pages are required, type 0.</p>                            </dd>                        </dlentry>                        <dlentry >                            <dt ># of VM 1G Hugepages Node <i >n</i></dt>                            <dd >                                <p >The number of 1GiB pages to reserve for VM use on                                    the NUMA Node. If no 1GiB pages are required, type 0.</p>                            </dd>                        </dlentry>                    </dl>                    <p >To see how many pages of a given size you can successfully                        request on a node (assuming that pages of another size are not also                        requested), hover over the Information icon next to the field.</p>                    <fig id="fig_zdt_vzd_cs" >                        <image href="jow1432129731308.image" id="image_blt_xzd_cs"  width="2.5in">                            <alt >TiS Update Hugepage Memory: Maximum Pages info</alt>                        </image>                    </fig>                    <p >Any unused memory is automatically allocated as 4K pages.</p>                            </li>            <li id="li_N100D6_N10039_N10029_N10001" >                <p >Click <uicontrol >Save</uicontrol>.</p>            </li>            <li id="li_N100EB_N10039_N10029_N10001" >                <p >Unlock the host and wait for it to be reported as                        <b >Available</b>.</p>            </li>        </ol>    </body></topic>